class Solution {
    public ListNode swapNodes(ListNode head, int k) {
        
        ListNode first = head;
        
        // Step 1: go to k-th node from start
        for(int i = 1; i < k; i++){
            first = first.next;
        }
        
        ListNode fast = first;
        ListNode second = head;
        
        // Step 2: find k-th from end
        while(fast.next != null){
            fast = fast.next;
            second = second.next;
        }
        
        // Step 3: swap values
        int temp = first.val;
        first.val = second.val;
        second.val = temp;
        
        return head;
    }
}
We are not changing the structure of the list
We are only swapping values inside nodes

So:
👉 The head never changes
